'''Phil Brignull''' (born 2 October 1960) is a former [[England|English]] [[football (soccer)|football]] [[defender (football)|defender]]. He started his career as a youth team player at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]. An England schoolboy international, he played just one game in all competitions for West Ham<ref>[http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=83&united=Phil_Brignull Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics Phil Brignull]</ref> before moving to [[Bournemouth A.F.C.|Bournemouth]] in August 1981. He was a member of the Bournemouth team which famously  knocked [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] out of the [[FA Cup]] in January 1984.<ref>[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/sport/article786175.ece Caught in Time: Bournemouth beat Manchester United, FA Cup, 1984]</ref>
He also played for [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]], [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]],  [[Newport County F.C.|Newport County]] and [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]].

